18/08/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The opposition Movement for Change (PzP) party announced on Sunday (August 17th) that opposition parties in the country intend to join forces in order to achieve a faster change of government. The anti-government coalition will be called the Union for a Free and Prosperous Montenegro, and will announce its platform soon. The PzP said there was room for everyone in the union, including NGOs and intellectuals. (Dan, Mina, Makfax - 17/08/08) 
